@*
    Example 7 — Multiple selects in one page.

    Each select gets a distinct `Name`. The `Name` plays two roles:
      1. It is the <select> `name`, so the two controls don't share state.
      2. It is the discriminator on the managed <link> element, so each
         select swaps its own stylesheet without stepping on the other.

    Note: the active `data-theme` attribute on <html> is set by whichever
    select fires last. If you want two truly independent regions, scope
    your theme CSS to a wrapping data-theme attribute via OnChange.
*@

@page "/examples/theme-select/multiple-selects"
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@using LilyDesignSystem.Blazor.Helpers

<section>
    <h2>Region A</h2>
    <ThemeSelect
        Label="Region A theme"
        Name="region-a"
        ThemesUrl="/assets/themes/"
        Themes="@(new[] { "light", "dark" })" />
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Region B</h2>
    <ThemeSelect
        Label="Region B theme"
        Name="region-b"
        ThemesUrl="/assets/themes/"
        Themes="@(new[] { "abyss", "cupcake", "dracula" })" />
</section>
